<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="201" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d201">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.34537/126.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Gonzales</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-07">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 7, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Referring to the treaty signed December 27, 1912, for the enlargement of
                            the Guantanamo Naval Station,<note n="2" xml:id="d201fn2">See the text
                                in <ref target="frus1912#pg_295">For. Rel. 1912, pp. 295</ref>–<ref target="frus1912#pg_297">297</ref>.</note> I hear through the
                            Secretary of State that the Senate is now ready to ratify the treaty.
                            Owing, however, to the expiration of the six months limit it will be
                            necessary to draw up and sign a new treaty. Identical treaty, with
                            change of Article V eliminating time limit, would be acceptable here.
                            Will the Department advise me as to what action it wishes taken in this
                            matter?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>